esses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n\n{{Voice-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name         = Grace Rolek\n| image        = Grace Rolek by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| alt          = \n| caption      = Rolek at [[Phoenix Comicon]] in November 2017\n| birth_name   = Grace Sakura Rolek<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gracerolek.com/about |title=About Grace Rolek |accessdate=November 13, 2017 |publisher=GraceRolek.com}}</ref>\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1997|10|10}}\n| birth_place  = [[Burbank, California]], U.S.\n| death_date   = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|death date\u2020|birth date\u2020}} -->\n| death_place  = \n| other_names  = \n| occupation   = Actress, voice actress, singer\n| years_active = 2004\u2013present\n| known_for    = \n| website      = {{url|gracerolek.com}}\n| home_town    = [[Valencia, California]], U.S.\n}}\n\n'''Grace Sakura Rolek''' (born October 10, 1997) is an American actress, voice actress and singer.\n\n==Career==\nRolek is known for voicing Connie Maheswaran on ''[[Steven Universe]]'', as well as for appearing in ''[[Happiness Is a Warm Blanket, Charlie Brown]]'' and ''[[Final Fantasy VII: Advent Children]]''. She also made voice acting appearances in ''[[Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs (film)|Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs]]'', ''[[Kung Fu Panda: Secrets of the Furious Five]]'' and ''[[Horton Hears a Who! (film)|Horton Hears a Who!]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://myfanfest.com/phoenix/project/grace-rolek/ |title=Grace Rolek - Phoenix Fan Fest |accessdate=November 13, 2017 |publisher=Phoenix Fan Fest |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171113165758/https://myfanfest.com/phoenix/project/grace-rolek/ |archive-date=November 13, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nShe made several public appearances as a guest of many [[Fan convention|fan conventions]] and gatherings, such as Cartoon Fair in France, or Beach City Con in Virginia Beach.\n\n==Personal life==\nRolek was born on October 10, 1997 in [[Burbank, California]] and began her career in voice acting in 2004.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1728847/ |title=Grace Rolek - IMDb |accessdate=November 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\nShe is of African-American, Italian, Polish and Japanese descent.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/grace_rolek/status/895099933233041408 |title=This is something I've wanted to bring up publicly for a while now, but uhhhh I'm mixed lmao (thread)|accessdate=October 12, 2018|website= Twitter |author= Grace Rolek}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n|+ Television roles\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" |Notes\n|-\n|2004\n|''[[George Lopez (TV series)|George Lopez]]''\n|Sara\n|Episode: \"E.I.? E.I. OH\"\n|-\n|2006\u20132008\n|''Lou and Lou: Safety Patrol''\n|Louise (voice)\n|Main role\n|-\n|2008\n|''[[Handy Manny]]''\n|Nelson (voice)\n|Episode: \"Bake Sale/Camping Tools\"\n|-\n|2009\n|''[[Special Agent Oso]]''\n|Molly (voice)\n|Episode: \"To Grandma with Love/Gold Flower\"\n|-\n|2013\u20132019\n|''[[Steven Universe]]''\n|[[List of Steven Universe characters#Connie Maheswaran|Connie Maheswaran]] (voice)\n|Main role\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Steven Universe Future]]''\n|Connie Maheswaran (voice)\n|Episode: \"Bismuth Casual,\" \"Together Forever,\" \"Growing Pains\", \"Everything\u2019s Fine\", \"I Am My Monster\", \"The Future\"\n|}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n|+ Film roles\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" |Notes\n|-\n|1984\n|''[[Nausica\u00e4 of the Valley of the Wind (film)|Nausica\u00e4 of the Valley of the Wind]]''\n|Child (voice)\n|English dub\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[Whisper of the Heart]]''\n|Additional voices\n|English dub\n|-\n|2004\n|''U.S. Air Marshals''\n|Little Girl\n|Short film\n|-\n|2004\n|''[[Mulan 2]]''\n|Additional voices\n|Direct-to-vid